generatedTitle: The Eastern Front in World War I

extractFactDictList.question: What was the Eastern Front in World War I?
extractFactDictList.sentence: The Eastern Front in World War I was a major theater of combat that included operations on the main Russian front as well as campaigns in Romania.

extractFactDictList.question: How long was the Eastern Front compared to the Western Front?
extractFactDictList.sentence: This front was more than twice as long as the Western Front.

extractFactDictList.question: Who were the main countries involved in the Eastern Front?
extractFactDictList.sentence: The entire frontier had the Russian Empire and Romania on one side; and the Central Powers (Austria-Hungary, Bulgaria, the Ottoman Empire, and Germany) on the other.
extractFactDictList.phrase: Russian Empire and Romania on one side; Central Powers on the other
